{{Quote|That's a myth so far as I'm concerned.|[[Mellor Yago]] on the ''Katana'' fleet|<ref name="Star Wars: Republic: Dreadnaughts of Rendili">''[[Star Wars: Republic: Dreadnaughts of Rendili]]''</ref>}}
The '''''Katana'' fleet''', also known as the '''Dark Force''' by some [[Journalist/Legends|journalists]], was a massive fleet of two hundred [[Dreadnaught-class heavy cruiser/Legends|''Dreadnaught''-class heavy cruisers]] launched by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] during its final years, as a major part of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate’s]] many grandiose projects. The fleet, however, was lost on its maiden voyage when a [[hive virus]] drove its crews insane and its [[Captain/Legends|captain]] jumped the ships blindly into [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]].

Five years after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] convinced smuggler [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Hoffner]] into providing the location of the long-lost task force. Having learned of Thrawn's target, the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] entered the race for the lost fleet as well. However, Thrawn's forces managed to escape with 178 of the prized ships before the Republic arrived.

==History==
===Creation===
In its waning decades, the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] threw money at many grandiose projects. One of them, which was completed in [[46 BBY/Legends|46 BBY]], was the ''Katana'' fleet, a task force of two hundred [[Dreadnaught-class heavy cruiser/Legends|''Dreadnaught''-class heavy cruisers]],<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> all carrying experimental [[All Terrain Personal Transport/Legends|AT-PT]] [[Walker/Legends|walkers]]. It was named after its [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the ''[[Katana]]''. To counter the high-staffing requirements of such vessels, the fleet was extensively modified with full-rig [[slave circuit]]ry, reducing the requirements to only about 2,200 per ship (instead of upwards of 16,000). To further distinguish the ''Katana'' fleet, [[Rendili StarDrive/Legends|Rendili StarDrive]] redesigned the entire Dreadnaught interior for the occasion, from the equipment and interior decor right down to the dark gray hull surfacing. The fleet earned the unofficial moniker "the Dark Force," partly because of the hull color, and partly because of the reduced need for interior lighting allowed by the smaller crew complements. With its advanced slave-rig technology, the ''Katana'' fleet was positioned to herald a new era for military warships.<ref name="Dark Force Rising" />

===Disappearance===
{{Quote|SBI believes this tyrannical genetics master to be not only Count Dooku's akk dog responsible for the recent stone mite outbreaks, but the homicidal maniac behind the carbonite metastasis crypts of Anaxes and the ''Katana'' fleet's descent into wholesale insanity.|Mace Windu, about Zeta Magnus' possible involvement|<ref name="swcw">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]''</ref>}}
However, what should have been a demonstration of efficiency turned into a complete fiasco. One or more of the ships' crewmen picked up a hive virus at one of the ports of call on the fleet's maiden voyage. Said virus, which had the particularity of driving its victims insane just before it killed them, was spread throughout all two hundred Dreadnaughts while in dormant state. When it suddenly flared up, the virus took down nearly everybody at once. The infected crewers, instead of calling for help, slaved their ships together. Because of that, the ''Katana'' command crew also descended into insanity and jumped blindly into [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], taking the entire fleet with them.<ref name="Dark Force Rising" />

Following that debacle, the ''Katana'' project became an embarrassment to the military echelons that had commissioned the fleet,<ref name="DB Dreadnaught">{{DB|starship|dreadnaught|Dreadnaught heavy cruiser}}</ref> and although that incident did not actually start the movement toward decentralization in automated ship functions, it certainly sealed its outcome.<ref name="Dark Force Rising" />

The incident made headlines for a time, with some [[Journalist/Legends|journalists]] making sarcastic word-plays on the "Dark Force" name. For a few years, many enthusiastic salvage teams hunted after it, but to no avail,<ref name="Dark Force Rising" /> as trying to find a ship that had misjumped to some random location in the galaxy was practically impossible, and even two hundred ships could easily be lost within the vastness of space.<ref name="Rogue Squadron">''[[X-Wing: Rogue Squadron]]''</ref> By the time of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the Republic's [[Senate Bureau of Intelligence/Legends|Senate Bureau of Intelligence]] surmised that the mastermind behind the [[hive virus]] had been [[Zeta Magnus]], a [[Geneticist/Legends|genetic]] [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorist]] affiliated with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], who was himself the result of a [[Accelerated Transgenic Heuristic Abhorer|freak experiment]] by the [[techno-lord]]s of the [[Arkanian Dominion]].<ref name="swcw" /> The fleet eventually became a legend, to the point that some people believed it had never existed in the first place.<ref name="Wedge's Gamble">''[[X-Wing: Wedge's Gamble]]''</ref>

===Rediscovery===
{{Quote|Out of the original two hundred Katana ships&hellip; there are fifteen left.|Talon Karrde|<ref name="Dark Force Rising" />}}
[[File:KatanaFleetRediscovery-DFR1.png|thumb|left|Captain Hoffner and his crew encountered two cruisers of the lost ''Katana'' fleet after a blind hyperspace jump.]]
The lost fleet remained undiscovered until smuggler [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Hoffner]] and his ship stumbled upon it in [[6 BBY/Legends|6 BBY]]. Hoffner and his navigator/sensor officer, [[Talon Karrde]] were the only ones aboard aware of the find, but neither realized the other person knew the secret. They each concealed the fleet's location until the right time to make use of it. Hoffner later arranged to sell individual ''Katana'' Dreadnaughts to [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]], who eventually accumulated a strike force of six of the ships, including his command ship, the [[Peregrine (Dreadnaught-class)|''Peregrine'']].

By [[6 ABY/Legends|6 ABY]], the balance of power between the New Republic, the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and warlord forces was so precarious that, despite their age, it was believed that any faction that recovered the fleet would immediately become the dominant force in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. The enormous potential value of the ''Katana'' fleet was used to draw the [[Imperial II-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial II''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Eviscerator/Legends|''Eviscerator'']] away as a prelude to the [[Second Battle of Borleias]].

[[File:Katana_skirmish.png|thumb|right|180px|Bel Iblis comes to the aide of the New Republic.]]
In [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], nearly fifty-five years after the fleet's disappearance, [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] became interested in obtaining the fleet. However, the Grand Admiral's actions turned [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] against the Galactic Empire and she, along with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], rescued Karrde from Thrawn's forces and brought the smuggler to the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. Thrawn was nonetheless able to acquire the information from Hoffner, and though both sides secured some of the fleet during the [[Battle for the Katana fleet|Battle for the ''Katana'' fleet]], Thrawn had acquired all but twenty-two of the Dreadnaughts before the New Republic forces arrived. These remaining vessels, except for the one Dreadnaught destroyed during the battle, became part of the New Republic fleet, along with the [[All Terrain Personal Transport/Legends|AT-PT]] [[Walker/Legends|walkers]] later used in the campaign against Thrawn. Initially, the New Republic believed Thrawn would not be able to take advantage of his new vessels, since he would require over three hundred thousand crewers for the ''Katana'' fleet&mdash;2,000 for each of the 178 ships. However, Thrawn proved to be more resourceful, using [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] produced in days from [[Spaarti cloning cylinder]]s in the Emperor's storehouse on [[Wayland/Legends|Wayland]] to crew his ships. Luke Skywalker and Talon Karrde estimated that Thrawn's clones were 'grown' to maturity in fifteen to twenty days instead of the typical year to three years. Clones grown this quickly were generally known to be [[Clone madness|mentally unstable]], but due to the use of [[Ysalamiri/Legends|Ysalamiri]] and their Force-neutralizing abilities, Thrawn's clones could be grown to perfection in a fraction of the typical time without this side effect.

Thrawn's acquisition of the ''Katana'' Dreadnaughts augmented his fleet's ability to the point that it was able to immediately attack more than twenty New Republic systems. In the later campaigns of Thrawn's fleet, it was a common vision to see a single Star Destroyer with several Dreadnoughts around, probably all from the ''Katana'' Fleet.<ref name="Before">''[[Before the Storm]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Talon Karrde stated that the fleet was lost "about ten years before the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]", which would relate to [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]] (at the time of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']]), but Captain [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]] set it at fifty-five years  prior to the date of ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'' and ''[[Dark Force Rising]]'', which is set in [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]]. This would correspond to [[46 BBY/Legends|46 BBY]]. ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' sets the fleet's completion prior to the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]], at the date given by Pellaeon (46 BBY), but does not implicitly state it was lost the same year.<ref>''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' p.33</ref> Later ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'' state that the fleet was ordered following the Stark Hyperspace War, on the behalf of the [[Militarists/Legends]] movement in the Senate, who lost their leader [[Ranulph Tarkin/Legends|Ranulph Tarkin]] during said war. Yet, the ''Atlas'' erroneously place the Stark Hyperspace War in 46 BBY and not in [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]] like the comic or the ''New Essential Chronology''.<ref>''[[The Essential Atlas]]'' p.140</ref>

However, [[Jorus C'baoth]] was listed as having been killed on board the ''Outbound Flight'' in the computer archives of the flagship, ''Katana''<ref name="The Last Command">''[[The Last Command]]''</ref>. Since the novel, [[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']], lists the deployment of the ''Outbound Flight'' as being in between ''The Phantom Menace'' and ''Attack of the Clones'' in [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]], this means the ''Katana'' fleet either was lost after the ''Outbound Flight'', or that the information in the ''Katana''{{'s}} computer about C'baoth was somehow updated after the ''Katana'' fleet was lost.

